25/03/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police arrested one of the alleged organisers and leaders of a suspected Wahhabi extremist group in Novi Pazar on Saturday (March 24th). 
The man, 30-year old Jasmin Smailovic, also known as Bilal, will remain in custody. 
On March 17th, police said that they found a training camp of Wahhabi extremists in the Novi Pazar region and seized a significant amount of explosives, maps and terrorist propaganda. 
Four men were arrested then, while a fifth suspect was apprehended three days ago. 
(Beta, B92, Tanjug, RTS - 24/03/07)
